  "text": "A matrigel tube formation assay was developed for testing of the anti-angiogenic activity of DZ1 based on the differentiation of HUVECs on Matrigel (BD Biosciences, Franklin Lake, NJ). Briefly, we first transfected CNE1-LMP1 or HNE2-LMP1 cells with DZ1 or CDN, and 24 h later, cells were trypsinized and centrifuged at 600 × g for 5 min. Approximately 5x10 [CITATION_1] cells and the same number of HUVECs (total number of cells was 1×10 [CITATION_2] ) were seeded in each well of a 24-well plate with 200 µl of embedded Matrigel. Next, the cells were incubated for 8 or 24 h, and the extent of microtubule-forming ability was examined using low magnification microscopy.",
